#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:-1
msgid ""
"Answers to common Spack questions, including version and variant selection, "
"package preferences, compiler configuration, and concretizer behavior, with "
"practical YAML and command-line examples."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:11
msgid "Frequently Asked Questions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:13
msgid ""
"This page contains answers to frequently asked questions about Spack. If you "
"have questions that are not answered here, feel free to ask on `Slack "
"<https://slack.spack.io>`_ or `GitHub Discussions <https://github.com/spack/"
"spack/discussions>`_. If you've learned the answer to a question that you "
"think should be here, please consider contributing to this page."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:20
msgid "Why does Spack pick particular versions and variants?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:22
msgid "This question comes up in a variety of forms:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:24
msgid ""
"Why does Spack seem to ignore my package preferences from ``packages.yaml`` "
"configuration?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:25
msgid ""
"Why does Spack toggle a variant instead of using the default from the "
"``package.py`` file?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:27
msgid ""
"The short answer is that Spack always picks an optimal configuration based "
"on a complex set of criteria\\ [#f1]_. These criteria are more nuanced than "
"always choosing the latest versions or default variants."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:32
msgid ""
"As a rule of thumb: requirements + constraints > strong preferences > reuse "
"> preferences > defaults."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:34
msgid ""
"The following set of criteria (from lowest to highest precedence) explains "
"common cases where concretization output may seem surprising at first."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:36
msgid ""
":ref:`Package preferences <package-preferences>` configured in ``packages."
"yaml`` override variant defaults from ``package.py`` files, and influence "
"the optimal ordering of versions. Preferences are specified as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:39
msgid ""
"packages:\n"
"  foo:\n"
"    version: [1.0, 1.1]\n"
"    variants: ~mpi"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:46
msgid ""
":ref:`Reuse concretization <concretizer-options>` configured in "
"``concretizer.yaml`` overrides preferences, since it's typically faster to "
"reuse an existing spec than to build a preferred one from sources. When "
"build caches are enabled, specs may be reused from a remote location too. "
"Reuse concretization is configured as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:50
msgid ""
"concretizer:\n"
"  reuse: dependencies  # other options are 'true' and 'false'"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:55
msgid ""
":ref:`Strong preferences <package-strong-preferences>` configured in "
"``packages.yaml`` are higher priority than reuse, and can be used to "
"strongly prefer a specific version or variant, without erroring out if it's "
"not possible. Strong preferences are specified as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:58
msgid ""
"packages:\n"
"  foo:\n"
"    prefer:\n"
"    - \"@1.1: ~mpi\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:65
msgid ""
":ref:`Package requirements <package-requirements>` configured in ``packages."
"yaml``, and constraints from the command line as well as ``package.py`` "
"files override all of the above. Requirements are specified as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:68
msgid ""
"packages:\n"
"  foo:\n"
"    require:\n"
"    - \"@1.2: +mpi\"\n"
"    conflict:\n"
"    - \"@1.4\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:77
msgid ""
"Requirements and constraints restrict the set of possible solutions, while "
"reuse behavior and preferences influence what an optimal solution looks like."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:80
msgid "How do I use a specific compiler?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:82
msgid ""
"When you have multiple compilers available in :ref:`spack-compiler-list`, "
"and want to build your packages with a specific one, you have the following "
"options:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:84
msgid ""
"Specify your compiler preferences globally for all packages in configuration "
"files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:85
msgid ""
"Specify them on the level of individual specs, like ``pkg %gcc@15`` or ``pkg "
"%c,cxx=gcc@15``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:87
msgid "We'll explore both options in more detail."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:90
msgid "Specific compiler for all packages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:92
msgid ""
"If you want to use a specific compiler for all packages, it's best to use :"
"ref:`strong preferences in packages.yaml config <setting-requirements-on-"
"virtual-specs>`. The following example prefers GCC 15 for all languages "
"``c``, ``cxx``, and ``fortran``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:95
msgid "Recommended: *prefer* a specific compiler"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:95
msgid ""
"packages:\n"
"  c:\n"
"    prefer:\n"
"    - gcc@15\n"
"  cxx:\n"
"    prefer:\n"
"    - gcc@15\n"
"  fortran:\n"
"    prefer:\n"
"    - gcc@15"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:110
msgid ""
"You can also replace ``prefer:`` with ``require:`` if you want Spack to "
"produce an error if the preferred compiler cannot be used. See also :ref:"
"`the previous FAQ entry <faq-concretizer-precedence>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:113
msgid ""
"In Spack, the languages ``c``, ``cxx`` and ``fortran`` are :ref:`virtual "
"packages <language-dependencies>`, on which packages depend if they need a "
"compiler for that language. Compiler packages provide these language "
"virtuals. When you specify these strong preferences, Spack determines "
"whether the package depends on any of the language virtuals, and if so, it "
"applies the associated compiler spec when possible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:117
msgid ""
"What is **not recommended** is to define ``%gcc`` as a required dependency "
"of all packages:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:119
msgid "Incorrect: requiring a dependency on a compiler for all packages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:119
msgid ""
"packages:\n"
"  all:\n"
"    require:\n"
"    - \"%gcc@15\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:128
msgid ""
"This is *incorrect*, because some packages do not need a compiler at all (e."
"g. pure Python packages)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:131
msgid "Specific compiler for individual specs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:133
msgid ""
"If different parts of your software stack need to be built with different "
"compilers, it's best to specify compilers as dependencies of the relevant "
"specs (whether on the command line or in Spack environments)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:135
msgid "Example of specifying different compilers for different specs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:135
msgid "$ spack install foo %gcc@15 ^bar %intel-oneapi-compilers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:141
msgid ""
"What this means is that ``foo`` will depend on GCC 15, while ``bar`` will "
"depend on ``intel-oneapi-compilers``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:143
msgid ""
"You can also be more specific about what compiler to use for a particular "
"language:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:145
msgid "Example of specifying different compilers for different languages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:145
msgid "$ spack install foo %c,cxx=gcc@15 %fortran=intel-oneapi-compilers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:151
msgid ""
"These input specs can be simplified using :doc:`toolchains_yaml`. See also :"
"ref:`pitfalls-without-toolchains` for common mistakes to avoid."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:157
msgid "How do I debug unexpected or failing concretization?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:159
msgid ""
"``spack install`` and ``spack concretize`` may fail with a concretization "
"error when the solver cannot find a package configuration that satisfies all "
"constraints."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:161
msgid ""
"Most of the time, the error message is structured and contains information "
"about which requirements could not be met. It typically identifies the "
"conflicting constraints and the files where they are defined (e.g., a "
"``packages.yaml`` entry or a ``conflicts()`` directive in a ``package.py``). "
"If the cause is clear from the error, you can fix the offending entry "
"directly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:165
msgid ""
"If it is not obvious *why* the solver made a particular decision -- for "
"example, why it chose a specific version or variant -- run :ref:`spack-"
"solve` to see the full optimization breakdown:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:167
msgid "$ spack solve <spec>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:171
msgid ""
"The output shows the optimization criteria and the weights assigned to each "
"choice. This makes it possible to trace which preference or requirement is "
"driving an unexpected result. See also :ref:`faq-concretizer-precedence` for "
"an overview of how criteria are prioritized."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:175
msgid ""
"For a deeper investigation of solver internals, see :ref:`debugging-"
"concretization` in the developer guide."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:178
msgid "Footnotes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:179
msgid ""
"The exact list of criteria can be retrieved with the :ref:`spack-solve` "
"command. See :ref:`faq-concretization-errors` for more information."
msgstr ""
